-- Taiwan Semi in Talks to Acquire Buildings, Land in Hsinchu From Powerchip
-- B y   J a n e t   O n g
-- 2010-12-27T01:06:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-27/taiwan-semiconductor-in-talks-to-buy-land-buildings-from-powerchip-tech.html
Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing
Co. is in talks to buy land, buildings from Powerchip Technology
Corp. in Hsinchu to expand, Elizabeth Sun, a spokeswoman for the
world’s largest contract chip manufacturer, said by telephone
today.  “Nothing has been finalized yet,” Sun said. She declined
to comment on a report by the Commercial Times TSMC plans to pay
Powerchip NT$3 billion for the acquisition.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Janet Ong at 
 jong3@bloomberg.net  